ssigned to the 3rd Squadron  7th U S  Cavalry Regiment  3rd Infantry Division at Fort Stewart GA  CPT Kupper deployed with 3 7 CAV in 2008 to the Adamiyah District of Bagdad  Iraq and quickly assumed duties as a Tank Platoon Leader  Following the deployment  CPT Kupper served as a Scout Platoon Leader and in 2009 deployed to Mosul  Iraq as a Troop Executive Officer and Squadron Battle Captain  In 2011 CPT Kupper completed the Maneuver Captains Career Course at Fort Benning GA and was assigned to 2nd Stryker Brigade Combat Team  2nd Infantry Division at Joint Base Lewis McChord  He deployed with the Brigade in 2012 to Kandahar  Afghanistan and served a Brigade Training Officer  Brigade Assistant Planner and as the Brigade Deputy Operations Officer  In 2013  CPT Kupper took command of A Company  52nd Infantry Regiment  Anti Tank  later reflagged to E Company  8th Squadron  1st United States Cavalry Regiment  After successfully completing command time  CPT Kupper was selected to serve as the Operations Officer for 8 1 CAV  CPT Kupper has deployed twice in support of Operation Iraqi Freedom  once in support of Operation Enduring Freedom and has four rotations to the National Training Center  His awards and decorations include the Bronze Star Medal  2 oak leaf clusters  Meritorious Service Medal  Army Commendation Medal  Army Achievement Medal  Combat Action Badge and the Parachutist Badge  He is married to his wife  Carolyn  from Virginia Beach VA      Captain Eric S  Kupper  Assistant Professor Military Science   Leadership 2066 Kilbourne Hall Virginia Military Institute Lexington  VA  24450 P   540  464 7819 E  kupperes vmi edu  CPT Eric S  Kupper is from Reading Pennsylvania and is a 2007 graduate of the Virginia Military Institute  He commissioned as an Army Second Lieutenant and was assigned to the 3rd Squadron  7th U S  Cavalry Regiment  3rd Infantry Division at Fort Stewart GA  CPT Kupper deployed with 3 7 CAV in 2008 to the Adamiyah District of Bagdad  Iraq and 